docs.snippet: A quarrel arises over a newsletter’s attempt to tie Campbell Brown, Facebook’s news head, to articles attacking Elizabeth Warren on a website she co-founded.
docs.lead_paragraph: A little more than two weeks after Facebook announced a news initiative, the social network was on the defensive, responding to a published report that a website co-founded by the company’s top news executive had displayed bias against Elizabeth Warren.

docs.abstract: More than 150 employees of WeWork sent a letter to management this week asking to be treated humanely as the company prepares to lay off thousands of people.
docs.snippet: More than 150 employees of WeWork sent a letter to management this week asking to be treated humanely as the company prepares to lay off thousands of people.
docs.lead_paragraph: More than 150 employees of WeWork sent a letter to management this week asking to be treated humanely as the company prepares to lay off thousands of people. The employees, who call themselves the WeWorkers Coalition, made clear their anger at the company’s co-founder and former chief executive, Adam Neumann, and implored WeWork’s leaders to treat them with “dignity.” Here’s what the letter said:

headline.main: ‘We Are Not the Adam Neumanns of This World’: What WeWork Employees Told Their Bosses

docs.abstract: The Ohio factory will be taken over by a venture that plans to hire 400 employees next year to make electric pickup trucks.
docs.snippet: The Ohio factory will be taken over by a venture that plans to hire 400 employees next year to make electric pickup trucks.
docs.lead_paragraph: General Motors has sold its factory in Lordstown, Ohio, to a company that says it will make electric pickup trucks with union labor at wages comparable to those of the Detroit automakers.

headline.main: Buyer of G.M. Lordstown Plant Promises Union Work and Wages
headline.print_headline: Strike Over, G.M. Sells Ohio Plant

docs.abstract: The cards, to be issued by some banks, will let customers use their chosen names. The goal is to avoid potential bias.
docs.snippet: The cards, to be issued by some banks, will let customers use their chosen names. The goal is to avoid potential bias.
docs.lead_paragraph: For transgender and nonbinary people, paying with a plastic card bearing a name that conflicts with their appearance can be stressful. The disconnect may provoke suspicion or hostility, advocates say, turning a simple shopping trip into a minefield.

headline.main: Mastercard to Offer Cards Aimed at Transgender and Nonbinary People
headline.print_headline: Fighting Bias With Names Etched in Plastic, Not Stone

docs.abstract: In a letter, workers asked executives to treat those who will lose their jobs humanely while giving people who remain more say in decisions.
docs.snippet: In a letter, workers asked executives to treat those who will lose their jobs humanely while giving people who remain more say in decisions.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the latest sign of worker activism in tech companies and start-ups, a group of employees at the struggling office-space giant WeWork are calling on management to treat workers humanely as the company prepares to lay off thousands, and to give workers a say in corporate decisions and policies.

headline.main: Awaiting Layoffs, WeWork Employees Say Founder’s Payout Is ‘Graft’
headline.print_headline: Hundreds Fearing Layoffs at WeWork Call Founder’s Payout ‘Graft’

byline.original: By Noam Scheiber, Peter Eavis and David Yaffe-Bellany
